==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grouper
<hw>Group"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr. Pg.
<ets>garupa</ets> crupper. Cf. <er>Garbupa</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of several species of valuable
food fishes of the genus <gen>Epinephelus</gen>, of the family
<fam>Serranid⟦ae⟧</fam>, as the red grouper, or brown snapper
(<spn>Epinephelus morio</spn>), and the black grouper, or warsaw
(<spn>Epinephelus nigritus</spn>), both from Florida and the Gulf of
Mexico.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The tripletail
(<gen>Lobotes</gen>).</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>In California, the name is
often applied to the rockfishes.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>groper</asp>, <asp>gruper</asp>, and
<asp>trooper</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

